**Basic conda commands:**
conda info
conda info --envs
conda list
python --versions
conda create -n (environment name) python = (version)
activate (environment name)
deactivate (environment name)
conda remove -n (env name) --all

conda install (package-name)
conda install -n (env name) (package name)
conda install -c (source repository) (package name)
conda update (package-name)
conda remove -n (env name) (package name)

Basic PIP commands:

pip install (package-name)
pip install (package wheel file) http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/

API-check functions of particular version of package
While installing packages, find compatibility between: package version+ python version + OS(windows/linux/MAC)

Must installed packages:
numpy
scipy
scikit-image
pandas
matplotlib
opencv
gdal
pyqt
